olive oil
1 carrot
1 packet beef mince
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet barbecue seasoning
1 packet tomato paste
1 bag baby spinach leaves
⅓ cup water
20 g butter
1 packet filo pastry
1 sachet mixed sesame seeds
1 Brown Onion
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Grate the carrot. Thinly slice onion.

Little cooks: Under adult supervision, older kids can help grate the carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook
beef mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add carrot and onion and cook until tender, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic paste, barbecue seasoning and tomato paste and cook until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add baby spinach leaves and the water, then stir until the spinach is wilted,
1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a splash more water if the filling looks too thick.

• Transfer beef filling to a baking dish and evenly sprinkle evenly with
shredded Cheddar cheese.
• In a small heatproof bowl, add the butter and microwave in 10 second
bursts until melted.
• Lightly scrunch each sheet of filo pastry and place on top of filling to
completely cover.
• Gently brush melted butter over pastry to coat and sprinkle with mixed
sesame seeds. Bake pie until golden, 15-20 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can add the finishing touch by sprinkling the cheese on top.

• Divide BBQ beef and filo pastry pie with veggies and Cheddar cheese
between bowls. Enjoy!